                    </a>
                </li>
            
        </ul>
    </div>

        </div>
    

            <div id="product-learning-points" class="product-half-row">
                
    
        
<div class="learning-points">
    <h3>In this book, you'll find:</h3>
    <ol>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <h5>Code Examples</h5>
                <p>Implement your workflow needs and avoid typical pitfalls with the help of code examples and step-by-step instructions.</p>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <h5>Detailed Scenarios</h5>
                <p>Understand interference in workflow processes: the use of BOR objects in agent determination, as well as data flow or event production.</p>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <h5>Practical Example</h5>
                <p>Explore a sample project, where you will follow explicit instructions for developing an ABAP Objects class and creating a BOR object for your workflow.</p>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <h5>Process Knowledge</h5>
                <p>Gain the discipline-specific programming knowledge the ABAP programming workflow process requires. This book shows you what's important to use in your daily work.</p>
            </li>
        
    </ol>
</div>


    

            </div>
            <div id="product-highlights" class="product-half-row">
                
    
        <div class="highlights">
     
    <h3>From the Contents:</h3>
    <ul>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <div>Workflow Engine</div>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <div>Workflow runtime</div>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <div>BOR and ABAP OO objects</div>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <div>Containers, work conditions, and data flows</div>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <div>Workflow patterns and tasks</div>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <div>Methods, work items, and events</div>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <div>Agent determination</div>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <div>Event definition and implementation</div>
            </li>
        
            <li style="color: #21B7C5;">
                <div>Workflow runtime system and log files</div>
            </li>
        
    </ul>
</div>

    


                
    
